{"id":75243,"title":"[The snoezelen as a form of caring].","abstract":"The concept of the snoezelen originated in The Netherlands. It is based on the stimulation of the senses and relaxation. It offers a unique opportunity for human contact between the caregiver and the patient, which helps to restore self-awareness and improve the distorted body percept. It emphasises the caring aspect of nursing.","date":"2014-08-20","categories":"Nervous System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25137963","annotations":[{"name":"Perception","weight":0.783697,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perception"},{"name":"Sense","weight":0.558165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sense"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.207031,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Netherlands","weight":0.14359,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netherlands"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Stimulation","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stimulation"},{"name":"Concept","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concept"},{"name":"Snoezelen","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snoezelen"},{"name":"Nursing","weight":0.0213102,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nursing"},{"name":"Grammatical aspect","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammatical_aspect"},{"name":"Distortion","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distortion"},{"name":"Relaxation technique","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relaxation_technique"},{"name":"Caregiver","weight":0.014492,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caregiver"}]}
